  "texts": [
    "In comparison to the \"Treatment of Disease\" relationship in the TFDR corpus, the remaining three types of relationships appear to be relatively scarce.",
    "This scarcity is reflected in lower macro-F1 scores compared to micro/weighted-F1 scores in RE downstream task.",
    "When training language models on highly imbalanced data, the lower macro-F1 score compared to the micro/weighted-F1 score highlights the challenges in handling class imbalance.",
    "This imbalance causes the model to be biased toward the majority class, leading to high performance on classes with more instances (reflected in the micro-F1) while underperforming on minority classes, which significantly lowers the macro-F1 score.",
    "The model struggles to learn meaningful representations for the minority classes due to insufficient data, leading to poor recall and precision for those classes."
